    "improvements_made": "Consolidated LOG_LIFECYCLE and OPERATION_HISTORY into a single AUDIT_EVENT entity to eliminate redundancy and capture all lifecycle and operational actions. Added creator reference (created_by_account_id) and timestamps (created_at, updated_at, deleted_at) to LOG for direct audit of creation and soft‑deletion. Introduced ROLE‑PERMISSION many‑to‑many relationship to model role‑based access control, removing the direct ACCOUNT‑PERMISSION link. Standardised attribute names to snake_case and included explicit foreign keys for category, creator, and audit links. Preserved existing strengths such as RBAC (OPERATOR‑ROLE), detailed operator/account separation, and comprehensive audit trail."
